OL,6,F"If you're thinking about making a
OL,7,Fvexatious complaint, if you're
OL,8,Fthinking about making a complaint and
OL,9,Fthere's no merit in that, then do know
OL,10,Fthat the police will take that serious
OL,11,Fin terms of tackling vexatious
OL,12,Fcomplaints and so I would urge you not
OL,13,Fto do it."
OL,15,FThe First Minister has repeatedly said
OL,16,Fthere is "disinformation" being spread
OL,17,Fabout the Bill and what it entails,
OL,18,Fclaiming there is a "triple lock" of
OL,19,Fprotection for speech.
